comments.body:
@aweiteka In principle plausible, as a counterpart to the read path in **EDIT<s>#147</s>https://github.com/containers/image/pull/147**.  But then there are details: What is the protocol and auth mechanism used for uploading the layers?

@runcom I am not really worried about manifest changes; this would obviously change the manifest and invalidate existing signatures, but it’s not the first such option; we already do layer compression and manifest schema conversion. The original author of the image can set `url`s and then sign; this would only prevent third parties from changing the URL list.

(OTOH there _have_ been vague suggestions that Fedora would like to do just that, edit the URL list of published manifests to be able to take advantage of their existing network of dumb file-serving mirrors. Too bad, at least for now, I suppose.  _Eventually_ we can think about `config.json`-based signatures, and it may even be necessary for local signature tracking, but I don’t think that should be our first choice.)
